%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EFor%20decades%2C%20people%20have%20been%20debating%20whether%20or%20not%20to%20implement%20daylight%20saving%20time.%20Several%20politicians%20and%20leaders%20have%20demanded%20that%20this%20biannual%20practice%20be%20discontinued.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EIn%20December%2C%20Donald%20Trump%20had%20criticised%20the%20biannual%20clock%20change%20on%20social%20media.%20Back%20then%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20Republican%20Party%20will%20use%20its%20best%20efforts%20to%20eliminate%20Daylight%20Saving%20Time%2C%20which%20has%20a%20small%20but%20strong%20constituency%2C%20but%20shouldn't!%20Daylight%20Saving%20Time%20is%20inconvenient%2C%20and%20very%20costly%20to%20our%20Nation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22allowfullscreen%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftruthsocial.com%2F%40realDonaldTrump%2F113647254141876924%2Fembed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHowever%2C%20a%20few%20months%20after%20strongly%20supporting%20permanent%20Daylight%20Savings%20Time%2C%20he%20called%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bfifty-fifty%20issue.%26quot%3B%20He%20said%20half%20of%20the%20people%20want%20to%20keep%20changing%20timings%20every%20autumn%20and%20fall%2C%20while%20the%20rest%20don't%20want%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EHe%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20something%20I%20can%20do%2C%20but%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20like%20it%20one%20way%2C%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20like%20it%20the%20other%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3ESenator%20Ted%20Cruz%20said%20that%20people%20would%20agree%20on%20stopping%20changing%20clocks%20twice%20a%20year%2C%20but%20there's%20disagreement%20on%20which%20time%20we%20should%20keep%20permanently.%20He%20said%20some%20want%20to%20extend%20evening%20sunlight%20as%20it%20is%20useful%20for%20playing%20sports%20and%20outdoor%20fun%2C%20while%20others%20prefer%20standard%20time%20as%20it%20leads%20to%20better%20sleep.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EEven%20in%202022%2C%20the%20bill%20proposed%20by%20the%20US%20Senate%2C%20led%20by%20Democrats%20at%20that%20time%2C%20urged%20the%20elimination%20of%20the%20twice-yearly%20changing%20of%20clocks.%20Since%20the%20Republican-controlled%20House%20did%20not%20take%20up%20the%20bill%2C%20it%20never%20reached%20then-President%20Joe%20Biden's%20desk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EDaylight%20saving%20time%20is%20basically%20when%20the%20clocks%20are%20moved%20forward%20by%20an%20hour%20every%20autumn.%20On%20November%202%2C%20the%20clocks%20'fall%20back%2C'%20meaning%20that%20the%20time%20will%20be%20set%20back%20one%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1744447080000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2F837figc8_donald-trump_625x300_12_April_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ftrump-wants-us-to-stop-changing-clocks-for-more-daylight-what-it-means-8146081%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22US%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20has%20once%20again%20called%20for%20an%20end%20to%20the%20practice%20of%20changing%20clocks%20for%20Daylight%20Savings%20Time.%20He%20urged%20Congress%20to%20stop%20shifting%20time%20twice%20a%20year%20as%20it%20adds%20an%20unnecessary%20financial%20burden%20on%20the%20country.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22The%20bags%20founders%2C%20venture%20capitalists%2C%20and%20other%20successful%20men%20are%20carrying%20to%20work%20in%202025%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bags%20for%20successful%20men.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67f964d7a466d2b74ab2fcac%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22900%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3ETumi%3B%20Getty%20Images%3B%20Chelsea%20Jia%20F