n%2FAnadolu%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ERussia's%20army%20has%20developed%20ways%20to%20rapidly%20target%20Ukraine's%20artillery.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAfter%20firing%2C%20a%20Ukrainian%20cannon%20can%20be%20pinpointed%20by%20counterbattery%20radars%20and%20attack%20drones.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ERussian%20tactics%20are%20rapidly%20evolving%20in%20ways%20likely%20to%20threaten%20NATO%20troops.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ERussia's%20military%20has%20the%20reputation%20of%20being%20a%20sledgehammer%2C%20as%20crude%20as%20it%20is%20destructive.%20This%20particularly%20applies%20to%20Russian%20artillery%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-artillery-war-ukraine-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bgod%20of%20war%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20isn't%20particularly%20concerned%20where%20his%20thunderbolts%20hit%20as%20long%20as%20they%20hit%20something.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20the%20difficult%20mission%20of%20counterbattery%20fire%20%E2%80%94%20using%20friendly%20artillery%20to%20destroy%20enemy%20artillery%20%E2%80%94%20bitter%20experience%20in%20Ukraine%20has%20taught%20Russian%20artillery%20to%20be%20more%20agile%20and%20sophisticated%2C%20in%20ways%20that%20could%20threaten%20NATO%20forces%20in%20a%20future%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20big%20guns%20have%20evolved%20from%20%26quot%3Ba%20machine%20that%20relied%20on%20mass%20to%20defeat%20its%20targets%20to%20one%20that%20has%20had%20to%20become%20leaner%20and%20more%20precise%20to%20survive%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchacr.org.uk%2F2025%2F01%2F23%2Fin-depth-briefing-86-from-mass-to-mass-precision%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20Center%20for%20Historical%20Analysis%20and%20Conflict%20Research%2C%20a%20British%20military%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImproved%20Russian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffired-generals-concerns-show-ukraine-bloodying-russia-in-key-fight-2023-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecounterbattery%20fire%3C%2Fa%3E%20has%20hampered%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20Ukraine's%20artillery%2C%20and%20that%20should%20worry%20more%20than%20Ukraine.%20%26quot%3BThe%20experience%20gained%20in%20Ukraine%20will%20lead%20to%20further%20doctrinal%20reforms%2C%20meaning%20that%20Western%20forces%20should%20expect%20to%20face%20similar%20weapons%20and%20tactics%2C%20techniques%20and%20procedures%20in%20the%20event%20of%20a%20war%20with%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20wrote%20Sam%20Cranny-Evans%2C%20who%20authored%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20with%20much%20else%20with%20the%20Russian%20armed%20forces%2C%20the%20place%20to%20start%20is%20the%20Soviet%20system.%20The%20Soviet%20Army%20devoted%20considerable%20artillery%20resources%20to%20suppressing%20enemy%20cannon%2C%20with%20entire%20battalions%20of%20howitzers%20and%20multiple%20rocket%20launchers%20allocated%20specifically%20to%20that%20mission.%20This%20goal%20was%20%26quot%3Ba%20constant%20pressure%20on%20the%20adversary's%20own%20fires%20assets%2C%20in%20what%20Western%20practitioners%20would%20term%20proactive%20counter-battery%20fires%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20explained.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20assumed%20that%20doing%20this%20would%20guarantee%20fire%20superiority%2C%20which%20in%20turn%20was%20deemed%20essential%20for%20success.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAgainst%20an%20opponent%20who%20fought%20Soviet-style%20%E2%80%94%20as%20Ukraine's%20military%20did%20and%20still%20does%3Cu%3E%2C%20%3C%2Fu%3Estrategies%20premised%20on%20relentless%20bombardment%20and%20large-scale%20frontal%20assaults%20%E2%80%94%20these%20tactics%20worked.%20%26quot%3BThis%20approach%20was%20relatively%20effective%20as%20long%20as%20Ukraine%20was%20concentrating%20its%20artillery%20and%20command%20and%20control%20nodes%2C%20as%20a%20battery's%20fire%20could%20be%20reasonably%20effective%20against%20a%20concentrated%20target%20in%20the%20vast%20Ukrainian%20plains%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20was%20that%20Ukraine%20eventually%20began%20dispersing%20its%20artillery%2C%20with%20lone%20cannon%20in%20different%20locations%20coordinating%20their%20fire.%20This%20forced%20Russia%20to%20use%20too%20many%20scarce%20cannon%20shells.%20%26quot%3BThe%20physics%20of%20the%20gunnery%20problem%20means%20that%20a%20single%20howitzer%20in%20a%20tree%20line%20is%20a%20very%20poor%20target%20for%20unguided%20fires%20from%20a%20battery%20of%20howitzers%20with%20limited%20ammunition%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20noted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Russia%20had%20a%20solution.%20In%202014%2C%20Russian%20drones%20provided%20targeting%20data%20to%20artillery%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdupuyinstitute.org%2F2017%2F03%2F29%2Fthe-russian-artillery-strike-that-spooked-the-u-s-army%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esmashed%3C%2Fa%3E%20three%20Ukrainian%20brigades%20in%20Donbas.%20It%20was%20an%20early%20example%20of%20Russia's%20%26quot%3Breconnaissance%20fire%20complex%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20drones%20and%20other%20reconnaissance%20systems%20provide%20real-time%20targeting%20data%20that%20enables%20Russian%20artillery%20and%20missiles%20to%20hit%20enemy%20forces%20before%20they%20have%20time%20to%20escape.%20Despite%20some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fduncanlmcculloch.substack.com%2Fp%2Freconnaissance-fires-complex-part%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglitches%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20this%20approach%20has%20worked%20surprisingly%20well%20given%20the%20usual%20rigidity%20of%20Russian%20command%20and%20control.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%20to%20the%20acoustic%20sensors%20and%20counterbattery%20radars%20that%20many%20armies%20use%20to%20detect%20enemy%20guns%2C%20Russia%20has%20added%20a%20variety%20of%20reconnaissance%20and%20attack%20drones%2C%20as%20well%20as%20guided%20artillery%20shells.%20The%20counterbattery%20process%20typically%20begins%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Funited24media.com%2Fwar-in-ukraine%2Frussias-killer-orlan-drone-and-its-western-manufactured-components-3265%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOrlan%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20searching%20for%20the%20muzzle%20flashes%20and%20thermal%20signatures%20of%20Ukrainian%20gun.%20The%20Orlan-30%20model%20is%20particularly%20dangerous%3A%20equipped%20with%20a%20laser%20designator%2C%20it%20can%20guide%20Krasnopol%20152-mm%20smart%20artillery%20shells%20to%20their%20target.%20Radar%20can%20be%20especially%20useful%20because%20it%20rapidly%20approximates%20a%20projectile's%20firing%20point.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Orlan-30%2C%20for%20example%2C%20can%20transmit%20video%20data%20up%20to%20120%20kilometers%20%5B75%20miles%5D%20and%20has%20an%20eight-hour%20endurance%2C%20enabling%20it%20to%20range%20deep%20into%20Ukraine's%20rear%20positions%20or%20loiter%20for%20extended%20periods%20over%20the%20frontline%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224428%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20Russian%20soldier%20operating%20a%20drone%20in%20an%20undisclosed%20location%20in%20Ukraine%20on%20January%2025%2C%202025%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c0678eb8b41a9673f9263b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222488%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20soldiers%20use%20drones%20to%20spot%20artillery%20that's%20fired%20and%20on%20the%20move%2C%20increasing%20the%20risks%20to%20artillery%20systems%20and%20their%20gunners.%3Cp%3ERussian%20Defense%20Ministry%20Press%20Service%20via%20AP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20Ukrainian%20artillery%20is%20pinpointed%2C%20Russian%20troops%20launch%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fkyivindependent.com%2Fhow-russias-homegrown-lancet-drone-became-so-feared-in-ukraine%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELancet%20loitering%20munition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20relays%20video%20back%20to%20a%20human%20controller%2C%20who%20decides%20when%20to%20crash%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-army-general-artillery-must-be-mobile-spread-out-survive-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuicide%20drone%3C%2Fa%3E%20into%20the%20target.%20This%20puts%20Ukrainian%20gunners%20in%20a%20dilemma.%20Standard%20procedure%20is%20for%20Ukrainian%20artillery%20to%20rapidly%20move%20after%20firing%2C%20before%20they%20can%20be%20hit%20by%20Russian%20guns.%20But%20this%20makes%20them%20visible%20to%20the%20cameras%20on%20the%20prowling%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-fighting-sees-new-drone-warfare-hit-to-kill-interceptions-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELancets%3C%2Fa%3E.%20If%20the%20Ukrainian%20gun%20still%20survives%2C%20any%20Orlan-30%20in%20the%20area%20can%20steer%20a%20Krasnopol%20shell%20to%20finish%20the%20job.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20points%20to%20the%20pro-Russian%20website%20Lostarmour%2C%20which%20claimed%20to%20have%20video%20of%20more%20than%202%2C700%20Lancet%20strikes%20in%20Ukraine%20as%20of%20early%20January%202025.%20These%20included%201%2C300%20attacks%20on%20Ukrainian%20artillery%2C%20of%20which%20more%20than%20a%20thousand%20resulted%20in%20the%20target%20being%20destroyed%20or%20damaged.%20If%20true%2C%20this%20%26quot%3Bindicates%20the%20growth%20in%20Lancet%20strikes%2C%20its%20importance%20in%20the%20counter-battery%20role%2C%20and%20the%20impact%20that%20it%20has%20had%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20perhaps%205%2C000%20artillery%20pieces%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Russia%20is%20also%20in%20the%20enviable%20position%20of%20having%20enough%20cannon%20to%20conduct%20counterbattery%20fire%20while%20still%20unleashing%20massive%20barrages%20against%20Ukrainian%20troops%20and%20fortifications.%20%26quot%3BIt%20should%20not%20be%20assumed%20that%20the%20practice%20for%20the%20counter-battery%20fight%20is%20detracting%20from%20the%20ability%20of%20the%20ground%20forces%20to%20conduct%20fires%20at%20scale%20in%20support%20of%20an%20offensive%20or%20defensive%20operation%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20warned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECurrent%20Russian%20artillery%20in%20Ukraine%20includes%20the%202S19%20Msta-SM2%20self-propelled%20152-mm%20howitzer%2C%20which%20has%20a%20range%20of%20up%20to%2025%20miles%20and%20a%20rate%20of%20fire%20of%2010%20rounds%20per%20minute.%20North%20Korea's%20M-1978%20Koksan%2C%20a%20self-propelled%20170-mm%20howitzer%20with%20a%20range%20of%20up%20to%2037%20miles%2C%20may%20also%20have%20been%20deployed%20to%20fight%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussia%20has%20also%20deployed%20an%20array%20of%20truck-mounted%20multiple%20launch%20rocket%20systems%20(MLRS)%2C%20including%20the%20new%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraines-air-defense-problems-are-letting-russia-launch-new-strikes-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ETornado-S%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%2012%20300-mm%20rockets%20(range%20of%20up%20to%2075%20miles)%20and%20the%20BM-27%20Uragan%20220-mm%20rocket%20system%20(range%20of%20up%20to%2045%20miles).%20While%20multiple%20rocket%20launchers%20were%20used%20for%20inaccurate%20but%20devastating%20saturation%20bombardment%20in%20World%20War%20II%2C%20modern%20Russian%20MLRS%20can%20also%20fire%20guided%20projectiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20counterbattery%20capabilities%20are%20continuing%20to%20evolve%2C%20with%20more%20automation%20and%20data%20networking%20speeding%20up%20response%20times.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20also%20evidence%20of%20direct%20linking%20between%20uncrewed%20aerial%20vehicles%20and%20howitzers%2C%20which%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20new%20form%20of%20counter-battery%20warfare%20in%20which%20lone%20guns%20are%20assigned%20an%20uncrewed%20aerial%20vehicle%20and%20magazine%20of%20guided%20rounds%20to%20find%20and%20engage%20howitzers%20at%20will%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20succes